<br>
Airmid groaned as his shield connected with her side, the pain ripping through her slender body. Falling to ground, a single tear rolled down her cheek, she desperately tried to call on Marr to heal her wounds, but she was too distracted to concentrate her pleas. This was no way for a Prietess to die, in a sleeping city, before a tavern, and by the sword of her own brother.<br>
<br>
&quot;You can't handle it any more? Can you Airmid? Can you!&quot;<br>
<br>
William's sword struck down firmly inches from her body, she tried to conjure the strength in her arms to pull herself away, but she found herself pressed against a stone wall. <br>
<br>
&quot;Answer me!&quot;<br>
<br>
Sheathing his sword he came down on top of her, strattling her lap, and grabbing her shoulders. He shook her violently, coaxing an answer, and with each shake she was slammed fiercely against the wall. The tears were turning into sobs, and this only angered the young Paladin more. A sharp stinging sensation erupted over her cheek, and her cries stopped, Airmid's once lively, cerulean eyes, stared off to the right, dull, lifeless. <br>
<br>
A short laugh escaped William's mouth, &quot;And you call yourself a Priestess of Marr.&quot;<br>
<br>
The truth was, she was. Just like her mother, THEIR mother. In their father's honor William had became a Paladin, but since he was a young boy he had never valued honor and valor. Today it showed, he was not the caliber to which Marr's Knights needed to be. He was a virus which need to be stopped, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Stop him now, my Child. I am here, I am watching over you...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
A wave of Red hair obstructed William's view as she turned her head to face him abruptly. In one swift motion she kneed him in the groin, and threw him off of her. Raising a hand to the heavens, Airmid frowned upon her brother cowering, as her ocean occuli turned red, &quot;And you called yourself a Paladin...&quot;<br>
<br>
Her voice hung in the air, it was strong, and unfaltering a major shift from what she had presented herself like before. This was what she was, strong. This is how it has been and always were to be, a woman out to do Mithaniel's bidding, with his watchful eye basking on her.<br>
<br>
William looked up to the sky, that was quickly covering with the darkest clouds he had ever seen. Glancing towards his sister, he couldn't believe it. As their eyes met, her salmon lips mouthed a word of fare well...<br>
<br>
Crimson lightning struck down, illuminating the streets, the power to which Marr aided Airmid in was incredible, but it lead her to commit a large offense, Fratricide.<br>
<br>
Dropping to her knees, tears began to run down her cheeks, as the crimson brilliance faded from her heavenly eyes. Looking to the sky, &quot;Forgive me...&quot; Was all she could muster before she passed out.<br>
<br>
