 her brother's death to answer. Singing softly the upbeat tune, he didn't want to disturb her reverence. After the gash on the back of her head and some other bruices and scraps were gone, Paren smiled. THe girl was only snifling now. &quot;COme on dear, we'll find someone who can help, do you know anyone in this city?&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ryvian>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 258<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/7/03 4:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=77>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hey dead week</span><hr size=1> Hey guys I know from experience that it's getting close to dead week so I understand that you all are getting ready for exams and winding down the year, but hear me if you are not back after your school year ends I'll be very upset... not that I could do a whole lot to any of you, but that would mean the site would die and that would suck for me, (who has already been looking for a new home just in case) <br>
